<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: SHEPPARD M-SERIES - STEERING SYSTEM DIAGNOSIS - INSPECT MECHANICAL COMPONENTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSPECT MECHANICAL COMPONENTS</title>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Check all front axle components for wear, looseness or seizing.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Inspect steering column for drag: more than 10 inch pounds (1.1 Nm) of drag measured with the
                    column suspended at the angle of operation is excessive.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Check steering gear mounting to be sure that it is tight. A steering gear that is shifting on the
                    frame will affect steering performance.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
